    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-06-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-06-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="352"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                <head>352. Memorandum of Conversation Between Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName> and Foreign Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d352fn0">Source: Department of State,
                        Conference Files: Lot 64 D 560, <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 1364.
                        Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName>. Two other
                        memoranda of conversation, in addition to Documents <ref target="#d353"
                            >353</ref> and <ref target="#d354">354</ref>, covering the London <hi
                            rend="italic">Times</hi> article and Hungarian credentials at the
                        International Labor Organization are in Department of State, Conference
                        Files: Lot 64 D 560, <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 1364.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1959-06-02T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 2, 1959, noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I spoke to <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Selwyn Lloyd</persName> about the fact that
                    I was cabling the President<note n="1" xml:id="d352fn1">See <ref target="#d355"
                            >Document 355</ref>.</note> suggesting he make a pretty strong statement
                    at his press conference to the effect that nothing that he had seen coming out
                    of Geneva would in any way justify a Summit Conference. To my great surprise, he
                    thought this was an excellent idea and that it might have great influence in
                    changing the atmosphere here so as to give us more hope of reaching some
                    agreement that would justify a Summit Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">C.A.H.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
